==Spanish==
===Etymology===
Mexican term for a U.S. Citizen, originally meaning ''foreigner'' or ''Greek''. (griego, as in "that's greek to me")
===Noun===
'''gringo'''
# (''many times offensive/derogatory'') A foreigner, often implying white and/or from the United States.

